<br>
A) Progression in the game takes place largely through gear at the higher end of the level range.<br>
<br>
B) Progression in gear is accomplished in medium to large groups.<br>
<br>
C) People like to feel like they have some value.<br>
<br>
D) There are basicly a handful of specialized roles, damage and healing in a raid.<br>
<br>
E) Skills that don't require skill, or at least give immediate feeback to the user making them feel like they've done something important don't make people feel useful (think summoning mod rods)<br>
<br>
So here we sit while they prepare to rebalance pure melee to keep up with the current bean counting going on and despite the fact that I'd love some more damage I wonder if something more creative than incrementing our damage could be done.<br>
<br>
As far as the rogue class I think there is a lot of room for improvement without touching overall damage at all.  Some ideas...<br>
<br>
1) Group Stealth.  This would enable rogues to extend the same protection they enjoy to nearby groupmates, leading them quietly through dangerous zones.  This could be added via AA and require shroud of stealth as a prerequisite.<br>
<br>
2) Spell interuption. 61+ backstabs would gain the ability to interupt in a manner similar to a bash.  Gained with chaotic stab.<br>
<br>
3) Burst Damage.  The rogue would be able to do one minute of backstab damage in one stab at the cost of greying out backstab for 2 minutes sacrificing overall damage for immediate damage.  Not usable on certain mobs like kunark dragons. Passive gain at 65.<br>
<br>
4) 2h 1 handed weapons.  Specificly 1h pierces with a neg 100% duel wield mod.  Allowing the rogue to give up all offhand damage for increased backstab damage.   Swapping weapons should start bs recycle time over though to prevent exploitive use of this.<br>
<br>
5) Implimentation of locked doors as previously described (fat chance I know)  Specificly apropriately named apropriately placed invisible npcs representing doors( like a stout wooden door).  Killing or despawning them with the pick locks skill unlocks the door until respawn.  However while picking can be done in a stealthy manner blowing or knocking it in can bring down agro from nearby social mobs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aerimusshadowborn>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 304<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/03 1:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wizards</span><hr size=1> Also in what manner do you think wizards could be improved without simply incrimenting damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xoshia>Xoshia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/03 1:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizards</span><hr size=1> 60+ Pillars would be a start imo.<br>
