<br>
What does that mean?  It means that as far as progression of NPC upgrades and PC upgrades has been basically more HPs and or more damage.  Very few mobs have truly unique sets of abilities that force you to adjust and think on your feet.  <br>
<br>
The poster made some rough suggestions.  Although group SoS would be VERY powerful and most likely overpowering, he starts the thinking toward creativity.  I'm afraid though that creative suggestions do little if the main way to kill mobs is the tried and true MT--CH chain--with damage dealers laying the rubber heavy to road.<br>
<br>
I've said it before long ago and I'll say it again, the game has evolved into a poorly DM'ed D&amp;D game.  Where the DM just kept upping the &quot;power&quot; of the players and thus had to keep ramping of the power of the creatures until...................you guessed it he's killing the gods themselves (no choice in that because he overpowers everything else).  <br>
<br>
That's poor design IMO.  There are so many things that designers could do to keep the game fun, the players progressing (and therefore excited about going forward), the encounters challenging, and past loot valuable.<br>
<br>
Carrot and stick approach is proven to work, but the implementation of such is where my frustration lies.  SOE's solution to everything is the just give better Ratio weapons, more hp's on items....  How about being more creative like giving items that have things like immunity to fire, Brilliance (actually raises your effective level by 10 thereby decreasing your resist rates and fizzle rates--and doesn't cap out like it does now), AA skill Wall of Force (creates a magical barrier in a 20 ft raidius around the caster that makes the people within the barrier completely immune to all effects for 2 rounds--stuns the caster for 10 sec and drains 1000 mana)...<br>
<br>
Give me anything that doesn't require the designers to to give melee 20 damage 15 delay weapons and casters 4k nukes.  Alas the game is too far gone IMO.  It's only about power and no subtlety. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fqubedf3povar>FqubedF3povar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/03 10:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: abilities</span><hr size=1> Heh just take D&amp;D rules book and look at the spells, or go play D&amp;D with someone who has some DMing experiance and you will get plenty of options. <br>
