<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27642" target="top">Gear that I found</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kyron>Kyron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 321<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/30/03 10:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: abilities</span><hr size=1> The sad truth is that every time SoE gives out a new ability, players quickly find ways to use that ability to gain &quot;trivialize&quot; certain encounters. The classic wizard example being manaburn. In a roleplaying sense, I do not see a problem with 13 high level wizards being able to kill sona, let alone a blue mob like gore. It seems obvious to me that this should be possible in a roleplaying sense. But the reality is that if 13 wizards can kill sona, they will do it over and over and over again and farm the mob for loot. This is the same problem with any ability that SoE might give any class that can be considered &quot;overpowered&quot; in a situation. It will be used to farm loot, experience, or bypass content. The design of EQ is flawed in this way. So much so that I suspect it is unfixable.<br>
<br>
I was actually shocked that SoE was willing to bring charms up to the level of power that they have, because it seems to me the trend has been to disable and reduce the usefullness of special abilities to force every encounter to be the standard healer/tank/dps setup.<br>
<br>
The benefit of SOE's slowness and reluctance to rapidly change things in this game has preserved the value of character advancement to a certain degree. That is one area where I think SOE has been reasonably successful. Sure, people have found exploits and gained massive advantage from them, but the game is not dominated with people using exploits to level. Most level fairly.<br>
<br>
